    "body": "This adds functional test coverage for the addnode connection cap documented by the `addnode` RPC and requested in #28635.\n\nThe new test starts ten regtest nodes without the framework default inter-node topology, adds nine persistent addnode entries to node0, checks that all nine entries are tracked by `getaddednodeinfo`, and verifies that only eight manual outbound connections are established. It also observes the cap over a short stability window.\n\nThis is intentionally scoped to the external `MAX_ADDNODE_CONNECTIONS` behavior. It does not try to cover the duplicate-addnode/thread-sleep scenario discussed in #28635.\n\nI reviewed the test against the RPC/P2P surface it exercises:\n- `addnode` keeps all nine persistent entries.\n- `getpeerinfo` reports exactly eight `manual` peers.\n- `getnetworkinfo()[\"connections_out\"]` remains at eight.\n\nTesting:\n- `python3 -m py_compile test/functional/rpc_addnode_limits.py`\n- `test/functional/rpc_addnode_limits.py --configfile=build-clang/test/config.ini`\n- `test/functional/rpc_net.py --configfile=build-clang/test/config.ini`\n- `git diff --check`",
